    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can use this Eclipse Plugin: <a href=\"http://marketplace.eclipse.org/node/491839#.UIlr8ZDwCUm\">http://marketplace.eclipse.org/node/491839#.UIlr8ZDwCUm</a>\nThis is a multi-line string editor popup. Place your caret in a string literal press <kbd>ctrl</kbd>-<kbd>shift</kbd>-<kbd>alt</kbd>-<kbd>m</kbd> and paste your text.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 8279356,
      "reputation" : 71,
      "user_id" : 6224542,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/5wxdA.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "zzg",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6224542/zzg"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1490324128,
    "last_edit_date" : 1490324128,
    "creation_date" : 1461134569,
    "answer_id" : 36735781,
    "question_id" : 2159678,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>See: <a href=\"https://github.com/11039850/monalisa-orm/wiki/Multiple-line-syntax\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Multiple-line-syntax</a></p>\n\n<p>It also support variables in multiline string, for example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String name=\"zzg\";\nString lines = \"\"/**~!{\n    SELECT * \n        FROM user\n        WHERE name=\"$name\"\n}*/;\nSystem.out.println(lines);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Output：</p>\n\n<pre><code>SELECT * \n    FROM user\n    WHERE name=\"zzg\"\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1629382,
      "reputation" : 4480,
      "user_id" : 1504248,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 71,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/284126fdb6c01b0f131ae76e7184dede?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Enyby",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1504248/enyby"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1525270340,
    "creation_date" : 1525270340,
    "answer_id" : 50136791,
    "question_id" : 2159678,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The <a href=\"https://github.com/Enyby/EclipsePasteAsJavaString\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">EclipsePasteAsJavaString</a> plug-in allows you to insert text as a Java string by Ctrl + Shift + V</p>\n\n<h1>Example</h1>\n\n<p>Paste as usual via Ctrl+V:</p>\n\n<p><code>some text    with tabs\nand new \nlines</code></p>\n\n<p>Paste as Java string via Ctrl+Shift+V</p>\n\n<p><code>\"some text\\twith tabs\\r\\n\" +\n\"and new \\r\\n\" +\n\"lines\"\n</code></p>\n"
  } ],
