  "closed_reason" : "Duplicate",
  "title" : "Paste a multi-line Java String in Eclipse",
  "body" : "<p>Unfortunately, Java has no syntax for multi-line string literals. No problem if the IDE makes it easy to work with constructs like </p>\n\n<pre><code>  String x = \"CREATE TABLE TEST ( \\n\"\n             + \"A INTEGER NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY, \\n\"\n            ...\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>What is the fastest way to paste a multi-line String from the clipboard into Java source using Eclipse (in a way that it automatically creates code like the above).</p>\n"
}